        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 10:49PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1049 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Brevard, or near Rosman, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Toxaway, Penrose, Connestee, Pleasant Ridge State Park, Etowah,
Jones Gap State Park, Cleveland, Rocky Bottom, Dupont State Forest,
and Little River In Transylvania County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
